f multidrug resistant bacterial infections. Possible scenarios of origin and ongoing evolution of adpA orthologous group in Streptomyces conclude this monograph. ABSTRACTING & INDEXING Regulatory Genes of AdpA Subfamily in Streptomyces: Function and Evolution is covered by the following services: Baidu Scholar Google Scholar Naviga (Softweco) Primo Central (ExLibris) ReadCube Semantic Scholar Summon (ProQuest) TDOne (TDNet) WorldCat (OCLC)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh  aStreptomyces, antibiotics, AdpA, AraC/XylS type regulators, transcriptional factors, morphogenesis.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2018 Englishz978311060420708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2018z9783110603200oZDB-23-DPM0 cprintz978311062776340uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9783110627770423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110627770/original  a978-3-11-060420-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DPMb2018